{
  "text": "If additional domain hits that score above the default reporting E-value threshold are tandem repeats of a neighboring domain that was detected at the default E-value threshold, they are reported irrespective of the domain architecture's frequency in the NR database. Figure 1 shows the result of such a live search, for a query sequence derived from the PDB structure 2WOZ (11), as tracked by MMDB [CITATION_1] . In this example, an additional hit to a domain model is reported which is already found several times in a tandem repeat arrangement.",
  "citation_candidates": [
